name: src/builder.js
Builder
description: Allows piecemeal creation of events.

name: add
description: adds a group of field->values to the events created from this builder.
examples:
<caption>using an object</caption>
  var honey = new libhoney();
  var builder = honey.newBuilder();
  builder.add ({
    responseTime_ms: 100,
    httpStatusCode: 200
  });

<caption>using an ES2015 map</caption>
  let map = new Map();
  map.set("responseTime_ms", 100);
  map.set("httpStatusCode", 200);
  builder.add (map);

name: addField
description: adds a single field->value mapping to the events created from this builder.
examples: builder.addField("responseTime_ms", 100);

name: addDynamicField
description: adds a single field->dynamic value function, which is invoked to supply values when events are created from this builder.
examples: builder.addDynamicField("process_heapUsed", () => process.memoryUsage().heapUsed);

params.name: name
params.description: the name of the field to add to events.

params.name: fn
params.description: the function called to generate the value for this field.

name: sendNow
description: creates and sends an event, including all builder fields/dyn_fields, as well as anything in the optional data parameter.
examples:
<caption>empty sendNow</caption>
  builder.sendNow(); // sends just the data that has been added via add/addField/addDynamicField.

<caption>adding data at send-time</caption>
  builder.sendNow({
    additionalField: value
  });

params.name: data
params.description: field->value mapping to add to the event sent.

name: newEvent
description: creates and returns a new Event containing all fields/dyn_fields from this builder, that can be further fleshed out and sent on its own.
examples:
<caption>adding data at send-time</caption>
  let ev = builder.newEvent();
  ev.addField("additionalField", value);
  ev.send();

name: newBuilder
description: creates and returns a clone of this builder, merged with fields and dyn_fields passed as arguments.
examples:
<caption>no additional fields/dyn_field</caption>
  let anotherBuilder = builder.newBuilder();

<caption>additional fields/dyn_field</caption>
  let anotherBuilder = builder.newBuilder({ requestId },
                                          {
                                            process_heapUsed: () => process.memoryUsage().heapUsed
                                          });

params.name: fields
params.description: a field->value mapping to merge into the new builder.

params.name: dyn_fields
params.description: a field->dynamic function mapping to merge into the new builder.

name: src/event.js
Event
description: Represents an individual event to send to Honeycomb.

name: add
description: adds a group of field->values to this event.
examples:
<caption>using an object</caption>
  builder.newEvent()
    .add ({
      responseTime_ms: 100,
      httpStatusCode: 200
    });

<caption>using an ES2015 map</caption>
  let map = new Map();
  map.set("responseTime_ms", 100);
  map.set("httpStatusCode", 200);
  let event = honey.newEvent();
  event.add (map);

name: addField
description: adds a single field->value mapping to this event.

name: addMetadata
description: attaches data to an event that is not transmitted to honeycomb, but instead is available when checking the send responses.

name: send
description: sends this event to honeycomb

name: src/libhoney.js
Libhoney
description: Represents a honeycomb context.  Each honeycomb context has

name: constructor
description: constructs a libhoney context.

name: sendEvent
description:
sendEvent takes events of the following form:

{
  data: a JSON-serializable object, keys become colums in Honeycomb
  timestamp [optional]: time for this event, defaults to now()
  writeKey [optional]: your team's write key.  overrides the libhoney instance's value.
  dataset [optional]: the data set name.  overrides the libhoney instance's value.
  sampleRate [optional]: cause us to send 1 out of sampleRate events.  overrides the libhoney instance's value.
}

name: add
description: adds a group of field->values to the global Builder.
examples:
<caption>using an object</caption>
  honey.add ({
    responseTime_ms: 100,
    httpStatusCode: 200
  });

<caption>using an ES2015 map</caption>
  let map = new Map();
  map.set("responseTime_ms", 100);
  map.set("httpStatusCode", 200);
  honey.add (map);

name: addField
description: adds a single field->value mapping to the global Builder.
examples: honey.addField("responseTime_ms", 100);

name: addDynamicField
description: adds a single field->dynamic value function to the global Builder.
examples: honey.addDynamicField("process_heapUsed", () => process.memoryUsage().heapUsed);

params.name: fn
params.description: function that will be called to generate the value whenever an event is created.

name: sendNow
description: creates and sends an event, including all global builder fields/dyn_fields, as well as anything in the optional data parameter.
examples:
<caption>empty sendNow</caption>
  honey.sendNow(); // sends just the data that has been added via add/addField/addDynamicField.

<caption>adding data at send-time</caption>
  honey.sendNow({
    additionalField: value
  });

params.name: data
params.description: field->value mapping to add to the event sent.

name: newEvent
description: creates and returns a new Event containing all fields/dyn_fields from the global Builder, that can be further fleshed out and sent on its own.
examples:
<caption>adding data at send-time</caption>
  let ev = honey.newEvent();
  ev.addField("additionalField", value);
  ev.send();

name: newBuilder
description: creates and returns a clone of the global Builder, merged with fields and dyn_fields passed as arguments.
examples:
<caption>no additional fields/dyn_field</caption>
  let builder = honey.newBuilder();

<caption>additional fields/dyn_field</caption>
  let builder = honey.newBuilder({ requestId },
                                 {
                                   process_heapUsed: () => process.memoryUsage().heapUsed
                                 });

params.name: fields
params.description: a field->value mapping to merge into the new builder.

params.name: dyn_fields
params.description: a field->dynamic function mapping to merge into the new builder.
